@0  = ~Jaheira, I do not want to part ways with you forever. Just wait for me here. I will return for you when I need your help again.~
@1  = ~Our paths have to separate right now, but they will cross again one of these days. I might seek your help again soon. Let us set up a meeting place somewhere in the city of Baldur's Gate.~
@2  = ~Our paths have to separate right now, but they will cross again one of these days. I might seek your help again soon. Let us set up a meeting place somewhere along the Sword Coast.~
@3  = ~On second thought, Jaheira, I want you to stay with the group.~
@4  = ~As well it should be. Gorion taught you as best he could, and evidently some of that knowledge has stuck after all.~
@5  = ~So be it, <CHARNAME>. I shall wait for you here.~
@6  = ~So be it, <CHARNAME>. We shall wait for you here.~
@7  = ~Perhaps it is for the best. I would rather be somewhere else, as you appear to be somewhat of a lost cause. You have some of Gorion's sense, but little of his wisdom.~
@8  = ~Perhaps it is for the best. I would rather be somewhere else, as you appear to be somewhat of a lost cause. You have some of Gorion's sense, but little of his wisdom. Come, Khalid, there are better places for us than this.~
@9  = ~Do you take me for a fool, <CHARNAME>? I would not wait here for all the treasures of Balduran!~
@10  = ~Farewell then.~
@11  = ~On second thought, I want you to stay with the group.~
@12  = ~Oh, I trust in your outstanding skills of survival. When you are out of here, go to the safe haven of your choice and wait for me there.~
@13  = ~Do you take me for a fool, <CHARNAME>? We would not wait here for all the treasures of Balduran!~
@14  = ~I shall wait for you at the Friendly Arm Inn. It is a perfect place to spend a few days recovering from the hardships of travel.~
@15  = ~When in Baldur's Gate, one should visit the Elfsong tavern. It is not a rule, rather a simple fact of life. <CHARNAME>, I will be there when you need me again.~
